  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver employs a power-law hemolysis model with three tunable configuration parameters: a base mesh element size (target 0.15 mm near blade surfaces), a Lagrangian particle-tracking time-step multiplier (0.02), and a hemolysis threshold shear stress (150 Pa). Validation results are reported at these chosen settings; however, no structured configuration node is linked to the package and the deployment context does not constrain or pin these values, creating a gap between validated and potentially deployed configurations.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-req",
