      "name": "Mesh convergence study — hemolysis index sensitivity",
      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) computed across three mesh densities (coarse 0.40 mm, medium 0.25 mm, fine 0.15 mm base element size). At the chosen fine-mesh setting, GCI for the normalized hemolysis index fell below 2.1%, satisfying the MRL 2 discretization requirement. Results are reported at the chosen settings; the specific mesh size value is documented in the study narrative but is not bound as a structured configuration parameter in this package.",
