      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental comparison — FDA GCBP hemolysis index",
      "description": "Simulated normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA GCBP experimental data across 5 flow-speed operating points. At the chosen Lagrangian time-step multiplier of 0.02 and hemolysis threshold shear stress of 150 Pa, mean absolute relative error was 8.4%, within the 15% acceptance band. These parameter values are referenced in the validation narrative but no structured node pins them for deployment.",
      "quantitativeResult": "Mean absolute relative error = 8.4%; all 5 operating points within acceptance band",
